children.text: The cladding in this area is not straight, which has resulted in a visible bow that looks poorly finished.
The Victorian Building Authority’s Guide to Standards and Tolerances clause 9.02 Straightness of Internal and External Wall Surfaces, states that
‘Walls are defective if they deviate from plane (bow) by more than 5mm over a 1.8m straight edge’ .
The builder warrants that the work will be carried out in
, which is not the case in this area, and will require the cladding be properly straightened in accordance with the above requirements.
